        <p class="tip" MadCap:autonum="&lt;b&gt;Tip: &lt;/b&gt;">Applying a single style to all objects is useful for standardizing branding. If you use a consistent color palette or line style in all of your <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture">images</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic">movies</MadCap:conditionalText>, you can use this feature to quickly apply a style to <MadCap:variable name="Other.Product" />'s standard loops, callouts, and arrows. Then you can use the Add to Palette feature to add these objects to a custom object palette<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.OnlineLive"> (see <MadCap:xref href="../../../Palettes/Adding_Objects_to_Palettes.htm" MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture">Adding Objects to Palettes</MadCap:xref><MadCap:xref href="../../../Palettes/Adding_Objects_to_Palettes_Mimic.htm" MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic">Adding Objects to Palettes</MadCap:xref>)</MadCap:conditionalText>.</p>
